            <li><a href="https://developers.google.com/identity/sign-in/web/sign-in">Google Sign-In</a> for user management</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.sqlite.org/">SQLite</a> for whiteboard persistence</li>
            <li><a href="https://webpack.github.io/">Webpack</a> to make up for ES5's lack of modules by bundling ES6 modules for the client</li>
            <li><a href="https://travis-ci.org/willprice/whiteboard">Travis CI</a> for continuous integration testing and deployment</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.heroku.com/">Heroku</a> for deployment</li>
            <li><a href="https://mochajs.org/">Mocha</a> for unit testing</li>
            <li><a href="http://chaijs.com/">Chai</a> for rich assertions in unit testing</li>
            <li><a href="http://sinonjs.org/">SinonJS</a> for mocks and spies in unit testing</li>
            <li><a href="https://inkscape.org/en/">Inkscape</a> for producing the site branding materials</li>
            <li><a href="https://www.gimp.org/">GIMP</a> for editing the screenshots used to produce the tutorial</li>
        </ul>
